  "text": "The MVCC compaction implementation in etcd-io/etcd spans two main packages:\n\n**Compaction scheduling** (`server/etcdserver/api/v3compactor/`): `compactor.go` defines the `Compactor` interface and factory function `New()` that selects between periodic and revision modes. `periodic.go` implements time-based compaction (`Periodic` struct) with a sliding window of recorded revisions. `revision.go` implements revision-based compaction (`Revision` struct) that compacts revisions older than a configured retention count every 5 minutes.\n\n**MVCC-level compaction** (`server/storage/mvcc/`): `kvstore.go` contains `store.Compact()` which updates the compact revision and schedules compaction via FIFO scheduler. `store.go` handles reading/writing scheduled and finished compact markers. `kvstore_compaction.go` contains `scheduleCompaction()` which performs the actual compaction: first compacting the in-memory B-tree index (`kvindex.Compact`), then batch-deleting superseded revisions from the backend store. `index.go` implements `treeIndex.Compact()` which walks the B-tree cloning and compacting each `keyIndex`. `key_index.go` implements per-key compaction logic (`keyIndex.compact()` and `doCompact()`) removing old revision generations.\n\n**Watch notification on compaction**: `watchable_store.go` contains `syncWatchers()` which calls `watcher_group.go`'s `chooseAll()` \u2014 this is where watchers whose `minRev < compactRev` receive a `WatchResponse{CompactRevision: compactRev}` and are marked as compacted. `watcher.go` defines the `WatchResponse` struct with `CompactRevision` field.\n\n**Slow watch detection**: `metrics.go` defines `slowWatcherGauge`. In `watchable_store.go`, watchers starting behind current rev go to `unsynced` group (incrementing `slowWatcherGauge`). The `notify()` method moves watchers that can't keep up (blocked channel) to victims, also incrementing the gauge. `syncWatchers()` resets the gauge based on unsynced + victim counts.",
